# Production server — port 3001 (mandatory)

The **production VPS** serves Dar Ul Quran via PM2 (`darulquran-next`) on **port 3001**, bound to **0.0.0.0**. Apache at darulquran.pk proxies to `http://127.0.0.1:3001/`.

**This is not configurable in production.** When `NODE_ENV=production`, `deploy/runtime.cjs` always uses port **3001** (ignores `PORT` in `.env`). **Never use port 3000.**

| Layer | File |
|-------|------|
| Source of truth | `deploy/runtime.cjs` |
| npm `dev` / `start` | `scripts/run-next.mjs` |
| PM2 process | `ecosystem.config.cjs` → `darulquran-next` |
| Reverse proxy | `deploy/apache.conf.example`, `deploy/nginx.conf.example` |
| CI health check | `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` |

When changing the listen port, update **all** rows above plus `.env.example` and the server `.env`. Never hardcode a different port in only one file.

`npm run start` and PM2 must pass `-H 0.0.0.0 -p 3001` via runtime config — not Next.js defaults.
